quran[58]{c,v,t}:
  37,145,So We cast him up onto the beach and he was sick
  37,146,and We caused a gourd tree to grow over him
  37,147,We sent him to a hundred thousand or even more
  37,148,They had iman and so We gave them enjoyment for a time
  37,149,"Ask them for a fatwa: does your Lord have daughters while they themselves have sons"
  37,150,"Or did We create the angels female, with them as witnesses"
  37,151,"No indeed, it is one of their blatant lies to say"
  37,152,´Allah has given birth´. They are truly liars
  37,153,Has He chosen daughters over sons
  37,154,What is the matter with you? How do you reach your judgement
  37,155,Will you not pay heed
  37,156,Or do you have some clear authority
  37,157,"Bring your Book, then, if you are telling the truth"
  37,158,They claim there is a blood-tie between Him and the jinn but the jinn know very well that they will be arraigned
  37,159,Glory be to Allah above what they describe —
  37,160,except for Allah´s chosen slaves
  37,161,You and those you worship
  37,162,you will entice no one to them
  37,163,except for him who is to roast in the Blazing Fire
  37,164,´There is not one of us who does not have a known station
  37,165,We are those drawn up in ranks
  37,166,We are those who glorify.´
  37,167,They used to say
  37,168,´If we had only had a Reminder from the previous peoples
  37,169,we would certainly have been sincere slaves of Allah!´
  37,170,But they have rejected it and they will soon know
  37,171,"Our Word was given before to Our slaves, the Messengers"
  37,172,that they would certainly be helped
  37,173,It is Our army which will be victorious
  37,174,Therefore turn from them for a time
  37,175,"And watch them, for they will soon see"
  37,176,Are they trying to hasten Our punishment
  37,177,When it descends in their courtyard — how evil will be the morning of those who were warned
  37,178,Therefore turn from them for a time
  37,179,"And watch, for they will soon see"
  37,180,"Glory be to your Lord, the Lord of Might, beyond anything they describe"
  37,181,And peace be upon the Messengers
  37,182,"And praise be to Allah, the Lord of all the worlds"
  38,1,Sâd By the Qur´an holding the Remembrance
  38,2,But those who are kafir are full of vainglory and entrenched in hostility
  38,3,How many generations We have destroyed before them! And they cried out when it was too late to escape
  38,4,"They are surprised that a warner should come to them from among themselves. The kuffar say, ´This is a lying magician"
  38,5,Has he turned all the gods into One God? That is truly astonishing!´
  38,6,"Their leaders went off saying, ´Carry on as you are! Hold fast to your gods. This is clearly something planned"
  38,7,We have not heard of this in the old religion. This is merely something contrived
  38,8,Has the Reminder been sent down to him out of all of us?´ They are in doubt about My Reminder. They have yet to taste My punishment
  38,9,"Or do they possess the treasuries of your Lord´s mercy, the Almighty, the Ever-Giving"
  38,10,"Or does the kingdom of the heavens and earth and everything between them belong to them? Let them, in that case, climb the ropes to heaven"
  38,11,Even a whole army of Confederates will be routed there
  38,12,"Before them the people of Nuh denied the truth, as did ´Ad and Pharaoh of the Stakes"
  38,13,and Thamud and the people of Lut and the Companions of the Thicket.* Those too were Confederates
  38,14,Each one of them denied the Messengers and so My punishment was justly carried out
  38,15,These people too are only awaiting a single Blast and it will not be repeated
  38,16,"They say, ´Our Lord, advance our share to us before the Day of Reckoning.´"
  38,17,"Be steadfast in the face of what they say and remember Our slave Dawud, who possessed true strength. He truly turned to his Lord"
  38,18,We subjected the mountains to glorify with him in the evening and at sunrise
  38,19,"And also the birds, flocking together, all of them turned to Him"
  38,20,We made his kingdom strong and gave him wisdom and decisive speech